Question: Should restaurant be required to display nutritional information in their menu?
Answer:
I think this issue has two sides. On one hand putting nutritional information on menu can show how healthy the food is and if the nutrition is desired by consumer. This means a lot to the ones on diet. However, on the other hand, most people will not read the menu in that detail and many nutrition names are hardly discernible. Also the restaurants can put wrong information on menu.